### How All Pieces Connect

```
[packages/shared/src/theme.ts]
  exports: ColorThemeDefinition objects, BuiltInColorTheme type,
           COLOR_THEME_DEFINITIONS, resolveColorTheme()
           ↓
[apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts]
  imports @t3tools/shared/theme
  on module load: reads localStorage → calls applyColorTheme()
    applyColorTheme() → reads COLOR_THEME_DEFINITIONS[resolvedId]
                      → calls document.documentElement.style.setProperty()
                          for all 28 CSS custom properties
                      → calls classList.toggle("dark", isDark)
  exports: useColorTheme() hook
           ↓                          ↓
[_chat.settings.tsx]          [ThreadTerminalDrawer.tsx] (optional future use)
  consumes useColorTheme()      could import applyColorTheme for xterm re-theme
  renders <ThemeSelector />
           ↓
[apps/web/src/index.css]
  @theme inline: --color-sidebar: var(--sidebar) etc.
    (Tailwind generates bg-sidebar, text-sidebar-foreground utilities)
  :root: fallback values for new vars
    (active before JS runs / as FOUC guard)
  All components using bg-sidebar, text-sidebar-foreground etc.
    continue to work as-is once the vars are defined
```

**Cascade priority (highest to lowest):**
1. `<html style="--background: #060810 ...">` (set by `applyColorTheme` via `style.setProperty`) — **wins**
2. `@variant dark { --background: ... }` inside `:root` block — overridden by #1
3. `:root { --background: ... }` — lowest, used as flash-of-unstyled-content guard

